    "body": "At the moment it is only possible to stack-allocate C++ objects using the default constructor.\r\nIt would be very interesting to allow creating objects on the stack using another constructor.\r\nE.g.\r\n```\r\ncdef extern from ...\r\n     cdef cppclass Foo:\r\n         Foo(int a)\r\n\r\n# possible syntax\r\ncdef myfunc():\r\n     # Clean but verbose\r\n     cdef Foo var = Foo(123)\r\n\r\n     # Short, C++ style\r\n     cdef Foo var(123)\r\n```",
